<main>
  <div style="background:#f5f5f5;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;padding:0.5rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:1100px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1rem;">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#666;">
        <a href="/" style="color:#01411C;">Home</a> &rsaquo;
        <a href="/#gas" style="color:#01411C;">Gas Bills</a> &rsaquo;
        <span style="color:#333;font-weight:600;">SNGPL Gas Bill</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Hero + Tool -->
  <section style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a4731 0%, #2d6a4f 100%); padding: 3rem 0; color: white;">
    <div class="container">
      <nav style="font-size:0.85rem; opacity:0.75; margin-bottom:1rem;">
        <a href="/" style="color:white;">Home</a> › <a href="/#gas" style="color:white;">Gas Bills</a> › SNGPL Gas Bill
      </nav>
      <h1 style="font-size:2.2rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">SNGPL Bill Online — Sui Northern Gas</h1>
      <p style="opacity:0.9; font-size:1.1rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">Check your SNGPL gas bill for Punjab, KPK, Islamabad, and AJK. Enter your 11-digit consumer number below.</p>
<p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> that covers both gas utilities — <a href="/sngpl-bill/">SNGPL</a> (Punjab, KPK, AJK) and <a href="/ssgc-bill/">SSGC</a> (Sindh, Balochistan) — alongside all 13 electricity DISCOs, <a href="/ptcl-bill/">PTCL</a>, and <a href="/water/">WASA water bills</a>. Check your <a href="/lesco-bill/">LESCO electricity bill</a> if you're in Lahore, or <a href="/iesco-bill/">IESCO</a> if in Islamabad. Open our <a href="/dashboard/">bill dashboard</a> to check all bills in one place, or learn <a href="/blog/how-to-pay-online/">how to pay bills online</a>.</p>

      <!-- Bill Checker Tool -->
      <div style="background:white; border-radius:16px; padding:2rem; max-width:560px; color:#1a1a1a;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">🔍 Check SNGPL Gas Bill</h2>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#555; margin-bottom:1rem;">SNGPL uses its own portal — enter your consumer number below to go directly to your bill.</p>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:0.5rem; margin-bottom:0.8rem;">
          <input id="sngpl-input" type="text" maxlength="11" placeholder="Enter 11-digit Consumer Number"
            style="flex:1; padding:0.75rem 1rem; border:2px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius:8px; font-size:1rem;"
            oninput="this.value=this.value.replace(/\D/g,'')" />
          <button onclick="checkSNGPL()"
            style="background:#1a4731; color:white; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border:none; border-radius:8px; font-weight:700; cursor:pointer; font-size:1rem;">
            Check Bill
          </button>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:0.75rem; color:#888;">Your 11-digit consumer number is on the top of any previous SNGPL gas bill</p>
        <div id="sngpl-error" style="display:none; color:#dc2626; font-size:0.85rem; margin-top:0.5rem;"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding: 3rem 1rem; display:grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap:2.5rem; max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto;">
    <div>

      <!-- About SNGPL -->
      <section id="about" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">About SNGPL — Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Limited</h2>
        <p>Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Limited (SNGPL) is Pakistan's largest natural gas utility, supplying gas to over <strong>7.3 million consumers</strong> across <strong>Punjab</strong>, <strong>Khyber Pakhtunkhwa</strong>, <strong>Islamabad Capital Territory</strong>, and <strong>Azad Jammu &amp; Kashmir</strong>. Incorporated in 1963, SNGPL operates the largest gas distribution network in the country — with pipelines running from the Sui gas fields in Balochistan to the northernmost cities of KPK.</p>
        <p>SNGPL supplies gas to major Pakistani cities including <strong>Lahore</strong>, <strong>Islamabad</strong>, <strong>Rawalpindi</strong>, <strong>Faisalabad</strong>, <strong>Multan</strong>, <strong>Gujranwala</strong>, <strong>Sialkot</strong>, <strong>Peshawar</strong>, <strong>Mardan</strong>, <strong>Abbottabad</strong>, <strong>Bahawalpur</strong>, <strong>Sargodha</strong>, and over 5,500 towns across the SNGPL service area. The company is listed on the Pakistan Stock Exchange and is jointly owned by the Government of Pakistan and private shareholders.</p>
        <p>SNGPL distributes both domestically produced natural gas (from Sui, Kandhkot, and other fields) and imported RLNG (Re-Gasified LNG from Qatar and UAE). During peak winter demand, RLNG accounts for 40–50% of SNGPL's supply mix — which directly impacts consumer tariffs.</p>
        <p>Gas regulation in Pakistan is handled by <strong>OGRA</strong> (Oil and Gas Regulatory Authority), which sets SNGPL's tariffs, monitors service quality, and adjudicates consumer complaints. OGRA is separate from NEPRA — electricity consumers escalate to NEPRA while gas consumers escalate to OGRA at <strong>0800-66256</strong> (toll-free).</p>
      </section>

      <!-- How to Check -->
      <section id="how-to-check" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">How to Check SNGPL Gas Bill Online — Step by Step</h2>
        <div style="background:#f0fdf4; border-left:4px solid #1a4731; padding:1.5rem; border-radius:8px; margin-bottom:1rem;">
          <p style="margin:0; font-weight:600; color:#1a4731;">Fastest method: Use the tool at the top of this page — enter your 11-digit consumer number and click Check Bill to be redirected directly to your bill on sngpl.com.pk.</p>
        </div>
        <ol style="line-height:2.5; padding-left:1.5rem;">
          <li>Find your <strong>11-digit SNGPL consumer number</strong> on the top of any previous gas bill</li>
          <li>Enter it in the tool above and click Check Bill — you go directly to the SNGPL portal</li>
          <li>Or visit <strong>sngpl.com.pk</strong> → Customer Services → View/Print Bill</li>
          <li>Enter your 11-digit consumer number and click Submit</li>
          <li>Your SNGPL bill appears with amount, due date, meter readings, and MMBTU consumption</li>
          <li>To save as PDF: press Ctrl+P and select Save as PDF as your printer</li>
          <li>Pay online through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or your bank app using the same consumer number</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Other Ways to Check Your SNGPL Bill</h3>
        <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin-top:1rem;">
          <thead style="background:#1a4731; color:white;">
            <tr><th style="padding:0.7rem; text-align:left;">Method</th><th style="padding:0.7rem; text-align:left;">How</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ["SNGPL App", "Download 'SNGPL' app from Google Play or App Store. Register with your consumer number and CNIC."],
              ["SMS Service", "Send your 11-digit consumer number to a number provided by SNGPL — check sngpl.com.pk for current SMS service"],
              ["WhatsApp", "SNGPL has a WhatsApp bill service — check sngpl.com.pk for the current WhatsApp number"],
              ["Phone", "Call SNGPL helpline 1199 — agent can tell you the amount and due date"],
              ["Bank Branch / ATM", "HBL, MCB, UBL, Meezan, Allied Bank — Bill Payment at counter or ATM"],
            ].map(row => (
              <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
                <td style="padding:0.7rem; font-weight:600;">{row[0]}</td>
                <td style="padding:0.7rem; font-size:0.9rem; color:#555;">{row[1]}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Reading the bill -->
      <section id="read-bill" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">How to Read Your SNGPL Gas Bill</h2>
        <p>SNGPL gas bills are structured differently from electricity bills. Here is every key field explained:</p>
        <div style="display:grid; gap:1rem; margin-top:1rem;">
          {[
            ["Consumer Number (11 digits)", "Your permanent 11-digit SNGPL account ID. Never changes. Use this for all online, SMS, and app-based bill checking. Also used for all payment apps."],
            ["Meter Reading (HCFT)", "Your gas meter records consumption in HCFT (Hundred Cubic Feet). The difference between Previous Reading and Current Reading gives you consumption in HCFT."],
            ["Consumption (MMBTU)", "SNGPL converts your HCFT consumption to MMBTU for billing. 1 MMBTU ≈ 10.03 HCFT. All tariff rates apply per MMBTU consumed."],
            ["Category", "Protected or Unprotected. Protected consumers (average ≤0.5 HCFT/day) pay the subsidized rate of Rs 400/MMBTU. Unprotected consumers face significantly higher rates. Your 6-month average determines category."],
            ["Gas Charges", "The core charge — your MMBTU consumption multiplied by your category's tariff rate (set by OGRA)."],
            ["GIDC (Gas Infrastructure Development Cess)", "A government levy charged per MMBTU, collected to fund gas infrastructure development."],
            ["GST (17%)", "General Sales Tax applied to the gas charges. Same as electricity — 17% on applicable charges."],
            ["Meter Rent", "Monthly rental for the gas meter. Typically Rs 20–100/month for domestic consumers."],
            ["Due Date", "Pay before this date to avoid the 10% late payment surcharge. SNGPL grace period: 7 days after due date."],
          ].map(row => (
            <div style="background:#f8f9fa; border-radius:8px; padding:1rem 1.25rem; border-left:3px solid #1a4731;">
              <h4 style="margin:0 0 0.3rem; color:#1a4731; font-size:0.95rem;">{row[0]}</h4>
              <p style="margin:0; font-size:0.9rem; color:#555;">{row[1]}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Tariff slabs -->
      <section id="tariff" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">SNGPL Gas Tariff Rates 2026 (OGRA Approved)</h2>
        <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse;">
          <thead style="background:#1a4731; color:white;">
            <tr>
              <th style="padding:0.8rem; text-align:left;">Consumer Category</th>
              <th style="padding:0.8rem; text-align:left;">Rate per MMBTU</th>
              <th style="padding:0.8rem; text-align:left;">Note</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {tariffSlabs2026.map((row, i) => (
              <tr style={`border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0; ${i===0?'background:#f0fdf4;':''}`}>
                <td style="padding:0.8rem;">{row.cat}</td>
                <td style="padding:0.8rem; font-weight:700; color:#1a4731;">{row.rate}</td>
                <td style="padding:0.8rem; font-size:0.85rem; color:#666;">{row.note}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:#888; margin-top:0.5rem;">Rates are OGRA-approved indicative figures. Verify exact rates on your bill or at ogra.org.pk. GST (17%) and GIDC apply additionally.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Coverage -->
      <section id="coverage" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">SNGPL Coverage Area — Which Cities Get SNGPL Gas?</h2>
        <p>SNGPL covers the following provinces and territories:</p>
        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:1rem; margin-top:1rem;">
          {[
            { prov: "Punjab", cities: "Lahore, Faisalabad, Rawalpindi, Multan, Gujranwala, Sialkot, Sargodha, Bahawalpur, Gujrat, Jhang, Sahiwal, Rahim Yar Khan, Kasur, Okara" },
            { prov: "KPK", cities: "Peshawar, Mardan, Abbottabad, Haripur, Nowshera, Swabi, Mansehra, Swat (urban), Kohat, D.I. Khan" },
            { prov: "Islamabad (ICT)", cities: "All Islamabad sectors, Blue Area, diplomatic enclave, industrial areas" },
            { prov: "AJK", cities: "Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Rawalakot, Kotli — select urban areas with pipeline access" },
          ].map(p => (
            <div style="background:#f8f9fa; border-radius:8px; padding:1rem; border-top:3px solid #1a4731;">
              <h4 style="margin:0 0 0.4rem; color:#1a4731;">{p.prov}</h4>
              <p style="margin:0; font-size:0.85rem; color:#555;">{p.cities}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:1rem; font-size:0.9rem;"><strong>Not covered by SNGPL:</strong> Karachi, Hyderabad, Sukkur, Quetta, and all of Sindh and Balochistan — these areas use <a href="/ssgc-bill/">SSGC (Sui Southern Gas Company)</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Saving Tips -->
      <section id="saving-tips" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:800; margin-bottom:1rem; color:#1a4731;">How to Reduce Your SNGPL Gas Bill — 8 Tips</h2>
        <div style="display:grid; gap:0.8rem;">
          {[
            "Stay under the 0.5 HCFT/day average to maintain Protected status. Protected consumers pay Rs 400/MMBTU vs Rs 1,597+ for Unprotected — a 75%+ saving.",
            "Insulate your home properly. In Lahore and Islamabad winters, poorly insulated rooms require twice as much gas heating. Weatherstripping, heavy curtains, and roof insulation dramatically cut heating gas use.",
            "Use an energy-efficient geyser. A 10-litre instant water heater uses 60% less gas than a traditional 35-litre storage geyser for the same hot water output.",
            "Fix gas leakages immediately. A dripping gas tap or faulty connection can consume 0.5–2 HCFT per day invisibly — equal to an entire household's daily usage.",
            "Cook with lids on pots. Covered cooking reduces gas use by 25–30% for the same cooking result.",
            "Service your gas appliances annually. Gas geysers and room heaters with clogged burners consume 20–30% more gas for the same heat output.",
            "Monitor SNGPL Protected/Unprotected status monthly. If you are borderline (0.4–0.55 HCFT/day), reducing usage in one month can prevent reclassification.",
            "Report gas theft in your neighbourhood. Gas theft from shared infrastructure inflates everyone's bills through system losses. Report to SNGPL at 1199 (anonymous).",
          ].map((tip, i) => (
            <div style="display:flex; gap:1rem; align-items:flex-start; background:#f8f9fa; border-radius:8px; padding:0.8rem 1rem;">
              <span style="background:#1a4731; color:white; width:28px; height:28px; border-radius:50%; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-weight:700; font-size:0.8rem; flex-shrink:0;">{i+1}</span>
              <p style="margin:0; font-size:0.9rem; color:#444;">{tip}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Complaint Process -->
      <section id="complaint" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
